'''David W. Collins''' worked for [[LucasArts]] as the lead sound designer and voice director with the video game division of the company and also served as an actor and voice actor for the company.

==Biography==
In [[2006]], Collins recorded [[death]] yells of [[stormtrooper]]s for the LucasArts [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[LEGO Star Wars II: The Original Trilogy]]'' because the LucasArts sound department did all of the vocalizations for the game at the time. The sound effects were eventually placed in the old LucasArts archive.<ref name="15 Easter Eggs">{{SW|url=news/lego-star-wars-holiday-special-easter-eggs|text=15 Easter Eggs to Find in the ''LEGO Star Wars Holiday Special''}}</ref>

Collins's most prominent ''Star Wars'' voice roles include [[PROXY]] in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]'', [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]] in ''[[Star Wars Battlefront: Renegade Squadron]]'', [[Grievous/Legends|General Grievous]] in ''[[Star Wars Battlefront: Elite Squadron]]'', and the [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] in [[Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith (video game)|''Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith'']], ''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]'', ''Star Wars Battlefront: Renegade Squadron'' and ''Star Wars Battlefront: Elite Squadron''.

Collins has served as a host at [[Celebration|Star Wars Celebrations]] [[Celebration IV|IV]], [[Celebration V|V]], and [[Celebration VI|VI]]. At Celebration VI in August 2012, he was inducted as an honorary member of the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]]. He also performed the role of [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] in the live performance of ''[[Star Wars: Smuggler's Gambit]]'', an original radio-style drama exclusive to the event.

Collins voiced several characters in the [[2015]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''Star Wars'': Episode VII ''The Force Awakens'']], including several [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtroopers]], [[Resistance]] soldiers and a Hangar Control Officer aboard the ''[[Finalizer]]''.<ref name="awakensvoices">{{SW|url=news/from-blast-that-x-wing-to-traitor-the-voices-of-star-wars-the-force-awakens|text=From "Blast that X-Wing!" to "Traitor!": The voices of ''Star Wars: The Force Awakens''}}</ref> He also provided additional voices in ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="Rogue One">''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>

Collins was the sound designer for the [[2020]] film ''[[The LEGO Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. For every trilogy era that [[Rey Skywalker]] [[time travel]]led to, Collins used specific sounds from that era to keep the authenticity. For example, the scene of the [[Battle of Yavin|trench run]] used sounds from [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|A New Hope]], scenes on the [[planet]]s [[Dagobah]] and [[Hoth]] used sounds from [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|The Empire Strikes Back]], the [[podracing]] scene on [[Tatooine]] used [[podracer]] sounds from [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|The Phantom Menace]], the scene on [[Exegol]] used lightning sounds from [[Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker|The Rise of Skywalker]], and the sound of [[Din Djarin]]'s [[The Mandalorian's IB-94 blaster pistol|blaster pistol]] from the ''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]'' was used for his cameo. Collins also found several vocalizations of [[Chewbacca's family]] from ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'' in the [[Skywalker Sound]] Library. He used those samples in the scene when Chewbacca's family showed up on the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]''. Collins also found stormtrooper death yells in the old LucasArts archive, and he incorporated the yells in the scene in which Rey and [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] [[Lightsaber duel|duel]] while travelling through [[portal]]s and various [[trooper]]s are flying around.<ref name="15 Easter Eggs" />

Collins acted as a sound effects editor for the series ''[[Star Wars: The Book of Boba Fett]]''.<ref name="Stranger">{{BOBF|Chapter 1: Stranger in a Strange Land}}</ref> He used an ARP 2600 synthesizer to create the sounds for the [[RX-Series pilot droid|RX-Series]] droid acting as a card dealer for the [[Chapter 1: Stranger in a Strange Land|premiere episode]].<ref name="Twitter RX">{{Twitter|DavidWCollins|status/1477772141588144128|David W. Collins|quote="Nowadays I've been making new ones on an arp 2600 synth (like the r3x casino card dealer in the first ep of #TheBookOfBobaFett"|archiveurl=https://archive.is/wip/hJeIf}}</ref>

He appeared at [[Celebration Anaheim (2022)|Celebration Anaheim]] in 2022,<ref name="CA">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-anaheim-2022-guest-announce-1|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration Anaheim Announces First Celebrity Guests}}</ref> where he hosted a ''[[Star Wars: The Bad Batch]]'' panel on [[May 29]].<ref name="Bad Batch Panel">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-celebration-the-bad-batch-panel|text=Fall In with ''Star Wars: The Bad Batch'' at ''Star Wars'' Celebration}}</ref>

